I really love this place! But I have to make one thing clear do not come to this restaurant before they close the staff will have an attitude and will serve you pretty cold food because they're upset. unto the review.  Pros: I mostly dine-in when I come here I never had a bad experience ordering food the portion sizes are huge and can feed a lot of people food is well seasoned well-prepared well cooked delicious a great spot to come to have lunch or dinner I'll mention this again please be considerate of the time when you dine in try not to dine in if they're about to close you will have a bad experience this place offers authentic Spanish food that's not salty and the cooks know what they're doing.  Cons:my only con  about this place is you may be craving a certain item on the menu That's not available because it's not that day that it's available for. their food selection is based off the day so if you wanted lasagna you would have to wait until the day that they actually have lasagna to serve otherwise really good experience I will say. The menu is a little hard to translate if you don't speak Spanish but to be very honest with you the staff is pretty helpful in trying to figure out what you want to order.
